# crontab.example — monitoruloficial.ro scraper
#
# Install on VPS:
#   crontab -e
#   paste / adapt the entries below
#
# All scripts use __file__-relative paths, so cwd doesn't matter.
# Edit REPO and PYTHON to match your VPS environment.
#
# Check your repo path:  realpath /path/to/repo
#
# ── Virtual environment ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Point PYTHON directly at the venv binary — do NOT use `source activate`.
# `source` only works in interactive shells; cron runs /bin/sh with no profile.
#
# If using a venv at /path/to/venv:
#   PYTHON=/path/to/venv/bin/python
#
# To find it on the VPS after creating/activating the venv:
#   which python     (while venv is active)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

REPO=/path/to/monitoruloficial
PYTHON=/path/to/venv/bin/python

# ── Twice-daily pipeline: index + ephemeral PDFs (Parts III–VII) ─────────────
# Runs at 10:00 and 22:00, Mon–Fri (gazette is only published on weekdays).
# main.py orchestrates: get_index.py → fetch_p3+.py
# Scripts log to $REPO/data/logs/mof.log; redirect cron stdout to /dev/null.

0 10,22 * * 1-5  $PYTHON $REPO/main.py >> /dev/null 2>&1

# ── Persistent PDFs (Parts I, II, PIM, V) ────────────────────────────────────
# Run once daily; only downloads what's missing (idempotent).
# On first run after VPS setup, add -start 2011-01-01 to skip empty pre-2011 rows.

30 10    * * 1-5  $PYTHON $REPO/fetch_pdfs.py >> /dev/null 2>&1

# ── Merge per-page PDFs into single documents ─────────────────────────────────
# Run after fetch_p3+.py has finished (offset by ~15 min to be safe).

15 10,22 * * 1-5  $PYTHON $REPO/concat_pages.py >> /dev/null 2>&1

# ── Optional: convert PDFs → Markdown ────────────────────────────────────────
# CPU-intensive; run once daily at a quiet time.
# Remove or comment out if text extraction isn't needed yet.

0 23     * * 1-5  $PYTHON $REPO/convert.py >> /dev/null 2>&1

# ── Notes ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Monitor runs:     python $REPO/stats.py
# Tail logs:        tail -f $REPO/data/logs/mof.log
# Check cron mail:  sudo journalctl -u cron (systemd) or /var/mail/$USER
